{
  "texts": [
    "In the segmentation phase, Mask R-CNN goes beyond bounding boxes to create pixel-level masks for individual objects, providing superior precision.",
    "It can accurately segment various objects, such as cars, cats, bicycles, or billboards, even in challenging conditions such as partial occlusion or shadowed regions.",
    "Mask R-CNN addresses key limitations of Faster R-CNN, such as the inability to segment individual objects within the same class or differentiate between multiple instances (e.g., distinguishing people in a crowd).",
    "It also reduces the computational overhead of storing intermediate features, thereby improving efficiency.",
    "By incorporating fine-tuning mechanisms, Mask R-CNN enhances detection accuracy and optimization, making it a robust solution for tasks such as autonomous navigation."
  ]
}